  "notes": "Lojban (la .lojban.) — constructed logical language, published by the Logical Language Group (1997 baseline, from Loglan 1955). Fully phonemic orthography: one letter = one phoneme. The apostrophe ⟨'⟩ is a voiceless glide /h/ occurring only between vowels; ⟨y⟩ is the schwa /ə/ used as a buffer/hesitation vowel. The sonorants m n l r may be syllabic. Period ⟨.⟩ marks an obligatory glottal pause and comma ⟨,⟩ a syllable break; neither is a phoneme and both are left unmapped. Stress falls on the penultimate syllable of Lojban words.",
